The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 India offer to fill in for Pak 

New Delhi: India have offered to stage Decembers Champions Trophy hockey tournament if it is moved from Pakistan for security reasons. 

Ive written to the FIH offering to host the event if they think of shifting it, Indian federation secretary K. Jothikumaran said on Friday. 

The tournament, scheduled to be staged in Lahore from December 1-9, has been thrown into doubt after Australia pulled out this week, citing safety concerns. 

Islamic militants have stepped up attacks in Pakistan since government forces stormed a prominent mosque in Islamabad to flush out suspected militants. (Reuters) 




